<abstract encodinganalog="520$a" label="Abstract:">In 1955, the Connecticut General Assembly authorized funding for the construction of a junior-senior high school in Mansfield, Connecticut, to be administered by the University of Connecticut.  The school opened in the fall of 1958 and remained a division of the UConn School of Education until the summer of 1987.</abstract>


